---> Sau khi g√µ  o  con tr·ªè s·∫Ω ƒë·∫∑t tr√™n d√≤ng v·ª´a m·ªü trong ch·∫ø ƒë·ªô So·∫°n th·∫£o.

  4. ƒê·ªÉ m·ªü m·ªôt d√≤ng ·ªû TR√äN con tr·ªè, ƒë∆°n gi·∫£n g√µ m·ªôt ch·ªØ	O hoa, thay cho
     ch·ªØ  o th∆∞·ªùng.  H√£y th·ª≠ th·ª±c hi·ªán tr√™n d√≤ng d∆∞·ªõi ƒë√¢y.
Di chuy·ªÉn con tr·ªè t·ªõi d√≤ng n√†y, r·ªìi g√µ Shift-O s·∫Ω m·ªü m·ªôt d√≤ng tr√™n n√≥.




~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
			B√†i 6.2: C√ÇU L·ªÜNH TH√äM V√ÄO


	     ** G√µ  a  ƒë·ªÉ ch√®n vƒÉn b·∫£n v√†o SAU con tr·ªè. **

  1. Di chuy·ªÉn con tr·ªè t·ªõi cu·ªëi d√≤ng ƒë·∫ßu ti√™n c√≥ k√Ω hi·ªáu --->
     b·∫±ng c√°ch g√µ  $	trong ch·∫ø ƒë·ªô c√¢u l·ªánh.

  2. G√µ  a  (ch·ªØ th∆∞·ªùng) ƒë·ªÉ th√™m vƒÉn b·∫£n v√†o SAU k√Ω t·ª± d∆∞·ªõi con tr·ªè.
     (Ch·ªØ  A  hoa th√™m vƒÉn b·∫£n v√†o cu·ªëi m·ªôt d√≤ng.)

Ch√∫ √Ω: L·ªánh n√†y thay cho vi·ªác g√µ  i , k√Ω t·ª± cu·ªëi c√πng, vƒÉn b·∫£n mu·ªën ch√®n,
     <ESC>, m≈©i t√™n sang ph·∫£i, v√† cu·ªëi c√πng, x , ch·ªâ ƒë·ªÉ th√™m v√†o cu·ªëi d√≤ng!

  3. B√¢y gi·ªù th√™m cho ƒë·ªß d√≤ng th·ª© nh·∫•t. Ch√∫ √Ω r·∫±ng vi·ªác th√™m gi·ªëng h·ªát v·ªõi
     vi·ªác ch√®n, tr·ª´ v·ªã tr√≠ ch√®n vƒÉn b·∫£n.

---> Dong nay cho phep ban thuc hanh
---> Dong nay cho phep ban thuc hanh viec them van ban vao cuoi dong.



~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
		    B√†i 6.3: M·ªòT C√ÅCH THAY TH·∫æ KH√ÅC


      ** G√µ ch·ªØ c√°i  R  hoa ƒë·ªÉ thay th·∫ø nhi·ªÅu k√Ω t·ª±. **

  1. Di chuy·ªÉn con tr·ªè t·ªõi cu·ªëi d√≤ng ƒë·∫ßu ti√™n c√≥ k√Ω hi·ªáu --->.

  2. ƒê·∫∑t con tr·ªè t·∫°i ch·ªØ c√°i ƒë·∫ßu c·ªßa t·ª´ ƒë·∫ßu ti√™n kh√°c v·ªõi d√≤ng c√≥ d·∫•u
     ---> ti·∫øp theo (t·ª´ 'tren').

  3. B√¢y gi·ªù g√µ R v√† thay th·∫ø ph·∫ßn c√≤n l·∫°i c·ªßa d√≤ng th·ª© nh·∫•t b·∫±ng c√°ch g√µ
     ƒë√® l√™n vƒÉn b·∫£n c≈© ƒë·ªÉ cho hai d√≤ng gi·ªëng nhau.

---> De cho dong thu nhat giong voi dong thu hai tren trang nay.
---> De cho dong thu nhat giong voi dong thu hai, go R va van ban moi.

  4. Ch√∫ √Ω r·∫±ng khi b·∫°n nh·∫•n <ESC> ƒë·ªÉ tho√°t, ƒëo·∫°n vƒÉn b·∫£n kh√¥ng s·ª≠a ƒë·ªïi s·∫Ω
	 ƒë∆∞·ª£c gi·ªØ nguy√™n.




~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
			    B√†i 6.4: THI·∫æT L·∫¨P C√ÅC THAM S·ªê

	  ** Thi·∫øt l·∫≠p m·ªôt t√πy ch·ªçn ƒë·ªÉ vi·ªác t√¨m ki·∫øm hay thay th·∫ø l·ªù ƒëi ki·ªÉu ch·ªØ **

  1. T√¨m ki·∫øm t·ª´ 'lodi' b·∫±ng c√°ch g√µ:
     /lodi
     L·∫∑p l·∫°i v√†i l·∫ßn b·∫±ng ph√≠m n.

  2. ƒê·∫∑t tham s·ªë 'ic' (Lodi - ignore case) b·∫±ng c√°ch g√µ:
     :set ic

  3. B√¢y gi·ªù th·ª≠ l·∫°i t√¨m ki·∫øm 'lodi' b·∫±ng c√°ch g√µ: n
     L·∫∑p l·∫°i v√†i l·∫ßn b·∫±ng ph√≠m n.

  4. ƒê·∫∑t c√°c tham s·ªë 'hlsearch' v√† 'incsearch':
     :set hls is

  5. B√¢y gi·ªù nh·∫≠p l·∫°i c√¢u l·ªánh t√¨m ki·∫øm m·ªôt l·∫ßn n·ªØa v√† xem c√°i g√¨ x·∫£y ra:
     /lodi

  6. ƒê·ªÉ x√≥a b·ªè vi·ªác hi·ªán s√°ng t·ª´ t√¨m th·∫•y, g√µ:
     :nohlsearch
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
			       T·ªîNG K·∫æT B√ÄI 6


  1. G√µ  o	m·ªü m·ªôt d√≤ng ph√≠a D∆Ø·ªöI con tr·ªè v√† ƒë·∫∑t con tr·ªè tr√™n d√≤ng v·ª´a m·ªü
     trong ch·∫ø ƒë·ªô So·∫°n th·∫£o.
     G√µ m·ªôt ch·ªØ  O  hoa ƒë·ªÉ m·ªü d√≤ng ph√≠a TR√äN d√≤ng c·ªßa con tr·ªè.

  2. G√µ  a  ƒë·ªÉ ch√®n vƒÉn b·∫£n v√†o SAU k√Ω t·ª± n·∫±m d∆∞·ªõi con tr·ªè.
     G√µ m·ªôt ch·ªØ  A  hoa t·ª± ƒë·ªông th√™m vƒÉn b·∫£n v√†o cu·ªëi m·ªôt d√≤ng.

  3. G√µ m·ªôt ch·ªØ  R  hoa chuy·ªÉn v√†o ch·∫ø ƒë·ªô Thay th·∫ø cho ƒë·∫øn khi nh·∫•n  <ESC>.

  4. G√µ ":set xxx" s·∫Ω ƒë·∫∑t tham s·ªë "xxx"









~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
		       B√†i 7: C√ÇU L·ªÜNH TR·ª¢ GI√öP


		      ** S·ª≠ d·ª•ng h·ªá th·ªëng tr·ª£ gi√∫p c√≥ s·∫µn **

  Vim c√≥ m·ªôt h·ªá th·ªëng tr·ª£ gi√∫p ƒë·∫ßy ƒë·ªß. ƒê·ªÉ b·∫Øt ƒë·∫ßu, th·ª≠ m·ªôt trong ba
  l·ªánh sau:
	- nh·∫•n ph√≠m <HELP> (n·∫øu b√†n ph√≠m c√≥)
	- nh·∫•n ph√≠m <F1> (n·∫øu b√†n ph√≠m c√≥)
	- g√µ   :help <ENTER>

  G√µ   :q <ENTER>   ƒë·ªÉ ƒë√≥ng c·ª≠a s·ªï tr·ª£ gi√∫p.

  B·∫°n c√≥ th·ªÉ t√¨m th·∫•y tr·ª£ gi√∫p theo m·ªôt ƒë·ªÅ t√†i, b·∫±ng c√°ch ƒë∆∞a tham s·ªë t·ªõi
  c√¢u l·ªánh ":help".  H√£y th·ª≠ (ƒë·ª´ng qu√™n g√µ <ENTER>):

	:help w
	:help c_<T
	:help insert-index
	:help user-manual


~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
		       B√†i 8: T·∫†O M·ªòT SCRIPT KH·ªûI ƒê·ªòNG

			  ** B·∫≠t c√°c t√≠nh nƒÉng c·ªßa Vim **

  Vim c√≥ nhi·ªÅu t√≠nh nƒÉng h∆°n Vi, nh∆∞ng h·∫ßu h·∫øt ch√∫ng b·ªã t·∫Øt theo m·∫∑c ƒë·ªãnh.
  ƒê·ªÉ s·ª≠ d·ª•ng c√°c t√≠nh nƒÉng n√†y b·∫°n c·∫ßn ph·∫£i t·∫°o m·ªôt t·∫≠p tin "vimrc".

  1. So·∫°n th·∫£o t·ªáp tin "vimrc", ph·ª• thu·ªôc v√†o h·ªá th·ªëng c·ªßa b·∫°n:
	:edit ~/.vimrc			ƒë·ªëi v·ªõi Unix
	:edit $VIM/_vimrc		ƒë·ªëi v·ªõi MS-Windows

  2. B√¢y gi·ªù ƒë·ªçc t·∫≠p tin "vimrc" v√≠ d·ª•:

	:read $VIMRUNTIME/vimrc_example.vim

  3. Ghi l·∫°i t·∫≠p tin:

	:write

  Trong l·∫ßn kh·ªüi ƒë·ªông ti·∫øp theo, Vim s·∫Ω s·ª≠ d·ª•ng vi·ªác hi·ªán s√°ng c√∫ ph√°p.
  B·∫°n c√≥ th·ªÉ th√™m c√°c thi·∫øt l·∫≠p ∆∞a th√≠ch v√†o t·∫≠p tin "vimrc" n√†y.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  B√†i h·ªçc h∆∞·ªõng d·∫´n s·ª≠ d·ª•ng Vim (Vim Tutor) k·∫øt th√∫c t·∫°i ƒë√¢y.  B√†i h·ªçc ƒë∆∞a ra
  c√°i nh√¨n t·ªïng qu√°t v·ªÅ tr√¨nh so·∫°n th·∫£o Vim, ch·ªâ ƒë·ªß ƒë·ªÉ b·∫°n c√≥ th·ªÉ s·ª≠ d·ª•ng
  tr√¨nh so·∫°n th·∫£o m·ªôt c√°ch d·ªÖ d√†ng. B√†i h·ªçc c√≤n r·∫•t xa ƒë·ªÉ c√≥ th·ªÉ n√≥i l√† ƒë·∫ßy
  ƒë·ªß v√¨ Vim c√≥ r·∫•t r·∫•t nhi·ªÅu c√¢u l·ªánh. Ti·∫øp theo xin h√£y ƒë·ªçc h∆∞·ªõng d·∫´n ng∆∞·ªùi
  d√πng: ":help user-manual".

  Cu·ªën s√°ch sau ƒë∆∞·ª£c khuy√™n d√πng cho vi·ªác nghi√™n c·ª©u s√¢u h∆°n:
	Vim - Vi Improved - T√°c gi·∫£: Steve Oualline
	Nh√† xu·∫•t b·∫£n: New Riders
  Cu·ªën s√°ch ƒë·∫ßu ti√™n d√†nh ho√†n to√†n cho Vim. ƒê·∫∑c bi·ªát c√≥ √≠ch cho ng∆∞·ªùi m·ªõi.
  C√≥ r·∫•t nhi·ªÅu v√≠ d·ª• v√† tranh ·∫£nh.
  H√£y xem: http://iccf-holland.org/click5.html

  Cu·ªën s√°ch ti·∫øp theo n√†y xu·∫•t b·∫£n s·ªõm h∆°n v√† n√≥i nhi·ªÅu v·ªÅ Vi h∆°n l√† Vim,
  nh∆∞ng c≈©ng r·∫•t n√™n ƒë·ªçc:
	Learning the Vi Editor - T√°c gi·∫£: Linda Lamb
	Nh√† xu·∫•t b·∫£n: O'Reilly & Associates Inc.
  ƒê√¢y l√† m·ªôt cu·ªën s√°ch hay v√† cho b·∫°n bi·∫øt t·∫•t c·∫£ c√°ch th·ª±c hi·ªán nh·ªØng g√¨ mu·ªën
  l√†m v·ªõi Vi. L·∫ßn xu·∫•t b·∫£n th·ª© s√°u ƒë√£ th√™m th√¥ng tin v·ªÅ Vim.

  B√†i h·ªçc h∆∞·ªõng d·∫´n n√†y vi·∫øt b·ªüi Michael C. Pierce v√† Robert K. Ware,
  Colorado School of Mines s·ª≠ d·ª•ng √Ω t∆∞·ªüng c·ªßa Charles Smith,
  Colorado State University.  E-mail: bware@mines.colorado.edu.

  S·ª≠a ƒë·ªïi cho Vim b·ªüi Bram Moolenaar.

  D·ªãch b·ªüi: Phan Vƒ©nh Th·ªãnh <teppi@vnlinux.org>, 2005
  Translator: Phan Vinh Th·ªãnh <teppi@vnlinux.org>, 2005
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀" Vim tutor support file
" Author: Eduardo F. Amatria <eferna1@platea.pntic.mec.es>
" Maintainer: Bram Moolenaar
" Last Change:	2016 Jul 16

" This Vim script is used for detecting if a translation of the
" tutor file exist, i.e., a tutor.xx file, where xx is the language.
" If the translation does not exist, or no extension is given,
" it defaults to the english version.

" It is invoked by the vimtutor shell script.

" 1. Build the extension of the file, if any:
let s:ext = ""
if strlen($xx) > 1
  let s:ext = "." . $xx
else
  let s:lang = ""
  " Check that a potential value has at least two letters.
  " Ignore "1043" and "C".
  if exists("v:lang") && v:lang =~ '\a\a'
    let s:lang = v:lang
  elseif $LC_ALL =~ '\a\a'
    let s:lang = $LC_ALL
  elseif $LANG =~ '\a\a'
    let s:lang = $LANG
  endif
  if s:lang != ""
    " Remove "@euro" (ignoring case), it may be at the end
    let s:lang = substitute(s:lang, '\c@euro', '', '')
    " On MS-Windows it may be German_Germany.1252 or Polish_Poland.1250.  How
    " about other languages?
    if s:lang =~ "German"
      let s:ext = ".de"
    elseif s:lang =~ "Polish"
      let s:ext = ".pl"
    elseif s:lang =~ "Slovak"
      let s:ext = ".sk"
    elseif s:lang =~ "Serbian"
      let s:ext = ".sr"
    elseif s:lang =~ "Czech"
      let s:ext = ".cs"
    elseif s:lang =~ "Dutch"
      let s:ext = ".nl"
    elseif s:lang =~ "Bulgarian"
      let s:ext = ".bg"
    else
      let s:ext = "." . strpart(s:lang, 0, 2)
    endif
  endif
endif

" Somehow ".ge" (Germany) is sometimes used for ".de" (Deutsch).
if s:ext =~? '\.ge'
  let s:ext = ".de"
endif

if s:ext =~? '\.en'
  let s:ext = ""
endif

" The japanese tutor is available in two encodings, guess which one to use
" The "sjis" one is actually "cp932", it doesn't matter for this text.
if s:ext =~? '\.ja'
  if &enc =~ "euc"
    let s:ext = ".ja.euc"
  elseif &enc != "utf-8"
    let s:ext = ".ja.sjis"
  endif
endif

" The korean tutor is available in two encodings, guess which one to use
if s:ext =~? '\.ko'
  if &enc != "utf-8"
    let s:ext = ".ko.euc"
  endif
endif

" The Chinese tutor is available in three encodings, guess which one to use
" This segment is from the above lines and modified by
" Mendel L Chan <beos@turbolinux.com.cn> for Chinese vim tutorial
" When 'encoding' is utf-8, choose between China (simplified) and Taiwan
" (traditional) based on the language, suggested by Alick Zhao.
if s:ext =~? '\.zh'
  if &enc =~ 'big5\|cp950'
    let s:ext = ".zh.big5"
  elseif &enc != 'utf-8'
    let s:ext = ".zh.euc"
  elseif s:ext =~? 'zh_tw' || (exists("s:lang") && s:lang =~? 'zh_tw')
    let s:ext = ".zh_tw"
  else
    let s:ext = ".zh_cn"
  endif
endif

" The Polish tutor is available in two encodings, guess which one to use.
if s:ext =~? '\.pl'
  if &enc =~ 1250
    let s:ext = ".pl.cp1250"
  endif
endif

" The Turkish tutor is available in two encodings, guess which one to use
if s:ext =~? '\.tr'
  if &enc == "iso-8859-9"
    let s:ext = ".tr.iso9"
  endif
endif

" The Greek tutor is available in three encodings, guess what to use.
" We used ".gr" (Greece) instead of ".el" (Greek); accept both.
if s:ext =~? '\.gr\|\.el'
  if &enc == "iso-8859-7"
    let s:ext = ".el"
  elseif &enc == "utf-8"
    let s:ext = ".el.utf-8"
  elseif &enc =~ 737
    let s:ext = ".el.cp737"
  endif
endif

" The Slovak tutor is available in three encodings, guess which one to use
if s:ext =~? '\.sk'
  if &enc =~ 1250
    let s:ext = ".sk.cp1250"
  endif
endif

" The Slovak tutor is available in two encodings, guess which one to use
" Note that the utf-8 version is the original, the cp1250 version is created
" from it.
if s:ext =~? '\.sr'
  if &enc =~ 1250
    let s:ext = ".sr.cp1250"
  endif
endif

" The Czech tutor is available in three encodings, guess which one to use
if s:ext =~? '\.cs'
  if &enc =~ 1250
    let s:ext = ".cs.cp1250"
  endif
endif

" The Russian tutor is available in three encodings, guess which one to use.
if s:ext =~? '\.ru'
  if &enc =~ '1251'
    let s:ext = '.ru.cp1251'
  elseif &enc =~ 'koi8'
    let s:ext = '.ru'
  endif
endif

" The Hungarian tutor is available in three encodings, guess which one to use.
if s:ext =~? '\.hu'
  if &enc =~ 1250
    let s:ext = ".hu.cp1250"
  elseif &enc =~ 'iso-8859-2'
    let s:ext = '.hu'
  endif
endif

" The Croatian tutor is available in three encodings, guess which one to use.
if s:ext =~? '\.hr'
  if &enc =~ 1250
    let s:ext = ".hr.cp1250"
  elseif &enc =~ 'iso-8859-2'
    let s:ext = '.hr'
  endif
endif

" Esperanto is only available in utf-8
if s:ext =~? '\.eo'
  let s:ext = ".eo.utf-8"
endif
" Vietnamese is only available in utf-8
if s:ext =~? '\.vi'
  let s:ext = ".vi.utf-8"
endif

" If 'encoding' is utf-8 s:ext must end in utf-8.
if &enc == 'utf-8' && s:ext !~ '\.utf-8'
  let s:ext .= '.utf-8'
endif

" 2. Build the name of the file:
let s:tutorfile = "/tutor/tutor"
let s:tutorxx = $VIMRUNTIME . s:tutorfile . s:ext

" 3. Finding the file:
if filereadable(s:tutorxx)
  let $TUTOR = s:tutorxx
else
  let $TUTOR = $VIMRUNTIME . s:tutorfile
  echo "The file " . s:tutorxx . " does not exist.\n"
  echo "Copying English version: " . $TUTOR
  4sleep
endif

" 4. Making the copy and exiting Vim:
e $TUTOR
wq! $TUTORCOPY
␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀===============================================================================
